              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "According to Wikipedia, **Euler's Identity** is an elegant mathematical equation given as \\( e^{i\\pi} + 1 = 0 \\). It blends five fundamental mathematical constants:\n\n1. \\( e \\) (Euler's number, around 2.71828...), the base of the natural logarithms.\n2. \\( i \\) (imaginary unit, satisfying \\( i^2 = -1 \\)).\n3. \\( \\pi \\) (approximately 3.14159...), the ratio of a circle's circumference to its diameter.\n4. 1 (multiplicative identity).\n5. 0 (additive identity).\n\nIt represents a special case of **Euler's formula**, \\( e^{ix} = \\cos x + i\\sin x \\), evaluated at \\( x = \\pi \\). This equation is celebrated for its mathematical beauty, connecting diverse fields such as geometry, algebra, and analysis. Some consider it the most beautiful or profound equation in mathematics.",
